# ============================================================================
# 📊 EXCLUSION SUMMARY
# ============================================================================
# Total exclusions: ~100+ file/folder types
# Estimated excluded size: 50GB+ (primarily datasets and cache)
# Security focus: API keys, passwords, certificates, financial data
# Development focus: Cache, temp files, IDE configs, build artifacts

# ============================================================================
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT REMINDERS
# ============================================================================
# 1. Never add actual passwords to .env.example (use CHANGE_ME placeholders)
# 2. Large datasets should be stored in external storage (S3, GCS, Azure Blob)
# 3. Model files (.pkl, .h5) should be stored in model registry, not git
# 4. Log files should go to centralized logging service
# 5. Database backups should be stored securely, not in git
# 6. Regular cleanup of temp/development files is recommended
# 7. Before committing, run: git clean -fd to remove untracked files
# 8. Use git-secrets or similar tools to prevent accidental commits of secrets

# ============================================================================
# 🚨  SECURITY QUICK CHECKLIST BEFORE COMMIT
# ============================================================================
# [ ] No actual passwords in .env files (only CHANGE_ME placeholders)
# [ ] No API keys or tokens in any committed files
# [ ] No certificate files (*.pem, *.key, *.crt)
# [ ] No large binary files (>10MB)
# [ ] No personal identification information
# [ ] No production database dumps or backups
# [ ] No financial or betting transaction data
# [ ] All sensitive data uses environment variables